data.title: James Brokenshire – POLITICO
data.meta_description: Latest news from POLITICO about James Brokenshire
data.text:
Dominic Raab appointed UK foreign secretary

Raab will also serve as first secretary of state — effectively deputy prime minister.

Jeremy Hunt snubs Cabinet job offer from Boris Johnson

Johnson’s leadership rival says he wants to be ‘a GOOD DAD!’

Liam Fox sacked in Boris Johnson Cabinet cull

A string of Cabinet ministers have been ousted.

May promotes former Europe minister in reshuffle

In the role of Cabinet Office minister, David Lidington will deputize at Prime Minister’s Questions.

British government imposes budget on Northern Ireland

The UK government says region’s local services will run out of money if budget isn’t passed.

UK government prepares to impose budget on Northern Ireland

Talks to restore power-sharing to Stormont have been unsuccessful.

Northern Ireland power-sharing talks close to collapse (again)

Sinn Féin and the Democratic Unionist Party fail to meet deadline.

Northern Ireland power-sharing talks to continue after UK election

UK government says bilateral discussions will continue.

UK government extends Northern Ireland talks deadline

The Northern Ireland secretary cited the June 8 election as the reason for the extension.

Strike deal or else, Northern Ireland secretary warns bickering parties

Northern Ireland’s political parties have been unable to form a ruling executive since an election last month.

Pensioner banned from feeding Northern Ireland parliament’s cats gets reprieve

Edna Watters, 76, was deemed a security risk and banned from the grounds.
